      <body>
        <div>
          <head rend="italic">A Dialogue betwixt <hi rend="roman">Time</hi> and a <hi rend="roman">Pilgrime</hi>.</head>
            <notatedMusic>
            <!-- MEI goes here -->
          </notatedMusic>
          <div type="underlay">
            <sp>
             <speaker rend="italic"><choice><abbr>Pilgr</abbr><expan>Pilgrime</expan></choice>.</speaker>
              <lg type="stanza">
                <l rend="indent1">AGed man that moves these fields.</l>
                  </sp></stage>
          </lg>
          <lg type="stanza">
            <stage><sp>
              <speaker rend="italic">Time.</speaker>
            <l rend="indent1">Pilgrime speak, what is thy will?</l>
            </sp></stage>
          <stage><sp>
            <speaker rend="italic"><choice><abbr>Pilgr</abbr><expan>Pilgrime</expan></choice>.</speaker>
            <l rend="indent1">Whose soile is this that such sweet Pasture yields?</l>
            <l>or who art thou whose Foot stands never still?</l>
            <l>or where am I?</l>
          </sp></stage>
          <stage><sp>
            <speaker rend="italic">Time.</speaker>
            <l rend="indent1">In love.</l>
          </sp></stage>
          <stage><sp>
            <speaker rend="italic"><choice><abbr>Pilgr</abbr><expan>Pilgrime</expan></choice>.</speaker>
            <l rend="indent1">His Lordship lies above.</l>
          </sp></stage>
          <stage><sp>
            <speaker rend="italic">Time.</speaker>
            <l rend="indent1">Yes and below, and round about</l>
            <l>where<pb n="2A2v"/> in all sorts of flow'rs are growing</l>
            <l>which as the early Spring puts out,</l>
            <l>Time fals as fast a mowing.</l>
          </sp></stage>
          <stage><sp>
            <speaker rend="italic"><choice><abbr>Pilgr</abbr><expan>Pilgrime</expan></choice>.</speaker>
            <l rend="indent1">If thou art Time, these Flow'rs have Lives,</l>
            <l>and then I fear,</l>
            <l>under some Lilly she I love</l>
            <l>may now be growing there.</l>
          </sp></stage>
          <stage><sp>
            <speaker rend="italic">Time.</speaker>
            <l rend="indent1">And in some Thistle or some spyre of grasse,</l>
            <l>my syth thy stalk before hers come may passe.</l>
          </sp></stage>
          <stage><sp>
            <speaker rend="italic"><choice><abbr>Pilgr</abbr><expan>Pilgrime</expan></choice>.</speaker>
            <l rend="indent1">Wilt thou provide it may?</l>
          </sp></stage>
          <stage><sp>
            <speaker rend="italic">Time.</speaker>
            <l rend="indent1">No.</l>
         </sp></stage>
          <stage><sp>
          <speaker rend="italic"><choice><abbr>Pilgr</abbr><expan>Pilgrime</expan></choice>.</speaker>
            <l rend="indent1">Alleage the cause.</l>
          </sp></stage>
            <stage><sp>
              <speaker rend="italic">Time.</speaker>
            <l rend="indent1">Because Time cannot alter but obey Fates Laws.</l>
          </sp></stage>
        </lg>
          <lg type="stanza">
            <stage><sp>
            <speaker><choice><abbr>Cho</abbr><expan>Chorus</expan></choice>.</speaker>
              <l>Then happy those whom Fate that is the stronger,</l>
              <l>together twist their threds, &amp; yet draws hers the longer.</l>
            </sp></stage>
         </lg>
       </div>
      </div>
